# Inbox parser UI (`InvoiceList.vue`)

## Parsed data for the dialog

- `parsedInvoices` ← `parserResultInvoices(data.parsed)` where `parsed` is `{ vendor_name, invoices: [...] }`
- `parsedInvoice` — computed tab selection from `parsedInvoices`
- **`POST /api/process-email/`** must populate `data.parsed` (backend: `parsed_envelope_for_process_result`)
- **`POST /api/test-parser/`** returns `result` only; persist via **`POST /api/persist-parsed/`** when vendor is selected (auto after Test Parser, or **Save to database**)

## Invoice / line item fields

Header list uses parser keys: `date_ordered`, `invoice_due_date`, `cust_po`, etc.

Line items: `id`, `job_id`, `job` (name), dimensions, qty, prices — use `formatLineItemField()`.

## Processing dialog layout

- Card class `processing-dialog`: fixed header + footer, scrollable `processing-dialog__body`
- Do not nest competing `overflow` on PDF panel and parsed-results; body scrolls as one

## API

Use `postAPI` / `putAPI` from `src/utils/api.js` — no hardcoded backend URLs.
